subject: p13473495
Findings: Redemonstration of moderate-to-severe cardiomegaly is noted. There is pulmonary vascular congestion consistent with edema. There is vague increased opacity at the left costophrenic angle which may reflect atelectasis versus a small pleural effusion. Redemonstration of a left subclavian venous stent is again noted. There is no evidence of pneumoperitoneum. Osseous structures are unchanged.
Impression: Opacity at left costophrenic angle likely reflects atelectasis vs. Pleural fluid. Pulmonary edema.
